FBIS4-49785 "drchi091_f_94002" FBIS-CHI-94-091 Daily Report 10 May 1994 Near East & South Asia Spokesman Comments on Evacuation of Citizens From Yemen Spokesman Comments on Evacuation of Citizens From Yemen OW1005113494 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1044 GMT 10 May 94 OW1005113494 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service Chinese BFN [Text] Beijing, 10 May (XINHUA) -- A Foreign Ministry spokesman today in Beijing answered a reporter's question and said that all Chinese in Yemen are safe and they will be evacuated from that country as quickly as possible. A reporter asked: Serious armed conflicts have broken out in Yemen recently, and various countries have evacuated their people from Yemen. Has China evacuated Chinese personnel from Yemen? The spokesman answered: On 5 May, armed conflict took place between south and north Yemen. The battles mainly took place in south Yemen. The Chinese Government is very much concerned about the safety of the Chinese diplomats, engineers, and workers there and has instructed our country's departments concerned to make arrangements for the evacuation of Chinese. As of this time, all personnel from our country in Yemen are safe and sound. Most Chinese people working in south Yemen have been evacuated safely to Djibouti by sea. The remaining people will also be evacuated as quickly as possible. The evacuation work is being carried out smoothly.
